    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Prioritize support tickets with Zendesk and Slack 24/7\n\n**Pattern:** Ticket Triage · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nPrioritize support tickets with Zendesk and Slack 24/7. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual escalation is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Slack → Open Zendesk Ticket → Collect All Outcomes → Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ticket triage without manual effort\n- Anyone automating escalation in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Responds in seconds\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenRouter API key; Slack OAuth2; Zendesk API token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "ff28cf8d-eb89-8b7f-c347-dc0b39b2e275",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "ecdf2801-aa61-1552-9a6d-ff56475fdded",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
